... which throws a `java.lang.ClassCastException` in the first call.

Finally note that you are also running the risk of a `java.lang.NullPointerException` if you don&#39;t known if your `getCodes` will return `null`. Replace for example `&quot;Always a string!&quot;` with `null` in the above code, and you will get a `java.lang.NullPointerException` in the *second* call.

